<p>The <code>@fields</code> property returns field name/value pairs from the current record as iterable data.</p>

<h2>Display All Fields</h2>
<pre>{open}users{close}
  {open}@first{close}
    &lt;table border="1"&gt;
    {open}@fields{close}
      &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;{open}$name{close}&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;{open}$value{close}&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    {open}/@fields{close}
    &lt;/table&gt;
  {open}/@first{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>

<p>Result (fields from first user):</p>
{users}
  {@first}
    <table border="1">
    {@fields}
      <tr><td>{$name}</td><td>{$value}</td></tr>
    {/@fields}
    </table>
  {/@first}
{/users}

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The <code>@fields</code> property is useful for dynamically displaying record contents without knowing the field names in advance. Each item has <code>$name</code> (field name) and <code>$value</code> (field value).</p>
